    "Generating synthetic data to augment the training dataset is one of the approaches that has been proposed for tackling the above challenges.",
    "Synthetic data generation can be done using classical methods such as SMOTE (Chawla et al., 2002; Quintana et al., 2020) or using advanced neural network-based generative models (Quintana et al., 2020; Das et al., 2021; Yoshikawa et al., 2021; Das and Spanos, 2022b).",
    "Another challenge is domain discrepancy.",
    "Thermal comfort, as per PMV, is dependent on six major parameters as described in the beginning of the section or, as per the adaptive thermal comfort model, is dependent on the outside temperature.",
    "However, it also varies from person to person, across climatic regions and economic conditions."
